The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 11 August is 60,569 (6,980.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 06 August, there were 2,445 new confirmed cases (281.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 30 July, there were 2,179 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 12% (266 extra cases).
